    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="458"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1031: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-06T10:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 6, 1933—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 4, February 4, 2 p.m.,<note n="95"
                        xml:id="d458fn95">Not printed.</note> Costa Rican Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs assures me he is cabling note to Peru invoking Kellogg Pact. Text of
                    such note will be transmitted to the Department when available.<note n="96"
                        xml:id="d458fn96">Note dated February 6, transmitted in despatch No. 1305,
                        February 7, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
